body_html: The one in tensorflow/user_ops is demonstrating user defined ops built with tf_custom_op_library, i.e., when you build custom operations with TF binary installed, the one in tensorflow/core/user_ops is demonstrating how you can build user ops with TF sources.

body: The one in `tensorflow/user_ops` is demonstrating user defined ops built with `tf_custom_op_library`, i.e., when you build custom operations with TF binary installed, the one in `tensorflow/core/user_ops` is demonstrating how you can build user ops with TF sources.
